sec.p:
The mass flux scheme represents an ensemble of coherent ascending thermal plumes in the grid cell as a mean plume. A model column is separated in two parts: the thermal plume and its environment. The vertical mass flux in the plume fth = ρ αthwth—where ρ is the air density, wth the vertical velocity in the plume and αth its fractional coverage—varies vertically as a function of lateral entrainment eth (from environment to the plume) and detrainment dth (from the plume to the environment):
