				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
				\usepackage{amsfonts}
				\usepackage{amssymb}
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$ {\frac{\partial f_{th}}{\partial z}}=e_{th}-d_{th} $$\end{document}For a scalar quantity q (total water, potential temperature, chemical species, aerosols), the vertical transport by the thermal plume (assuming stationarity) reads
2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
