				\begin{document}$$ {\frac{\partial {f_{th}}{q_{th}}}{\partial z}}=e_{th} q -d_{th} {q_{th}} $$
\end{document}qth being the concentration of q inside the plume (air is assumed to enter the plume with the concentration of the large scale, which is equivalent to neglect the plume fraction αth in this part of the computation). The time evolution of q finally reads
